Macam macam Distribusi Statistik di R

Distribusi Beta

x <- seq(0,1,0.01)

data <- data.frame(
  x = x,
  y1 = dbeta(x, 0.5,0.5),
  y2 = dbeta(x, 0.2,0.9),
  y3 = dbeta(x, 4,1),
  y4 = dbeta(x, 2,3),
  y5 = dbeta(x, 5,5)
)

labels <- c(
  "alpha = 0.5, beta = 0.5",
  "alpha = 0.2, beta = 0.7",
  "alpha = 4, beta = 1",
  "alpha = 2, beta = 3",
  "alpha = 5, beta = 5"
)
data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=x)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y1, color = labels[1]), size = 1.1) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y2, color = labels[2]), size = 1.1) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y3, color = labels[3]), size = 1.1) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y4, color = labels[4]), size = 1.1) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y4, color = labels[5]), size = 1.1) +
  guides(color = guide_legend(title = "Parameter")) +
  theme_minimal() + ylab("f(x)") + ggtitle(
    "Distribusi Beta",
    "Parameter alpha mempengaruhi perubahan di sebelah kiri grafik\nparameter beta memengaruhi perubahan di sebelah kanan grafik"
  )

Distribusi Binomial

n <- 49
x <- seq(0,n)
data <- data.frame(
  x = x,
  "p0" = dbinom(x, n, 0),
  "p0.1" = dbinom(x, n, 0.1),
  "p0.5" = dbinom(x, n, 0.5),
  "p0.9" = dbinom(x, n, 0.9),
  "p1" = dbinom(x, n, 1)
)

color <- viridis::inferno(5)
fill <- c()
fill[c("0","0.1","0.5","0.9","1")] = color

data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x)) +
  geom_col(aes(y = p0, fill = "0")) +
  geom_col(aes(y = p0.1, fill = "0.1")) +
  geom_col(aes(y = p0.5, fill = "0.5")) +
  geom_col(aes(y = p0.9, fill = "0.9")) +
  geom_col(aes(y = p1, fill = "1")) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = fill) +
  guides(fill = guide_legend(title = "Probabibilitas")) +
  ggtitle(
    "Distribusi Binomial dengan\nbeberapa parameter P", 
    subtitle = "Parameter p memengaruhi perubahan kemencengan"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() + ylab("f(x)")

Distribusi Cauchy

Distribusi Cauchy memiliki 2 parameter :

X0, dan Gamma

x <- seq(-5,5,0.01)

data <- data.frame(
  x = x,
  "x0g0.5" = dcauchy(x, location = 0, scale = 0.5),
  "x0g1" = dcauchy(x, location = 0, scale = 1),
  "x0g5" = dcauchy(x, location = 0, scale = 5),
  "xmin3g1" = dcauchy(x, location = -3, scale = 1),
  "x3g1" = dcauchy(x, location = 3, scale = 1)
)

labels <- c(
  "X0 = 0, Gamma = 0.5",
  "X0 = 0, Gamma = 1",
  "X0 = 0, Gamma = 5",
  "X0 = -3, Gamma = 1",
  "X0 = 3, Gamma = 1"
)

data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = x0g0.5, color = labels[1]), size = 2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = x0g1,   color = labels[2]), size = 2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = x0g5,  color = labels[3]), size = 2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = xmin3g1,color = labels[4]), size = 2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = x3g1,   color = labels[5]), size = 2) +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = wesanderson::wes_palette("Darjeeling1")
  ) +
  guides(color = guide_legend(title = "Parameters")) +
  ggtitle(
    "Distribusi Cauchy\nDengan Beberapa Parameter",
    "Scale (gamma) merubah kurtosis sedangkan Location (x0) merubah lokasi"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() + ylab("f(x)")

Distribusi Chi Square

x <- seq(0,20, 0.01)

data <- data.frame(
  x = x,
  y1 = dchisq(x, df = 2),
  y2 = dchisq(x, df = 3),
  y3 = dchisq(x, df = 5),
  y4 = dchisq(x, df = 7),
  y5 = dchisq(x, df = 10)
)

labels <- c(
  "2",
  "3",
  "5",
  "7",
  "10"
)
color <- c()
color[labels] = viridis::plasma(length(labels))

data %>% ggplot(aes(x=x)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y1, color = labels[1]), size = 1.4) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y2, color = labels[2]), size = 1.4) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y3, color = labels[3]), size = 1.4) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y4, color = labels[4]), size = 1.4) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y5, color = labels[5]), size = 1.4) +
  scale_color_manual(values = color) +
  guides(color = guide_legend(title = "Degree of Freedom")) +
  ggtitle(
    "Distribusi Chi Square\nDengan Degree of Freedom yang berbeda",
    "df mempengaruhi kurtosis sekaligus kemencengan distribusi.\nSemakin besar df, maka kurva akan semakin landai dan semakin tidak menceng"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +ylab("f(x)")

Distribusi Gamma

Distribusi gamma di R memiliki parameter

  • scale (\(\beta\))
  • rate (\(\theta\))
  • shape (\(\alpha\))

ingat bahwa \(\beta = 1/\theta\)

x <- seq(0,15,0.01)

data <- data.frame(
  x = x,
  y1 = dgamma(x, 0.5, 2),
  y2 = dgamma(x, 1, 2),
  y3 = dgamma(x, 3, 2),
  y4 = dgamma(x, 5, 2),
  y5 = dgamma(x, 7, 2),
  y6 = dgamma(x, 1, 3),
  y7 = dgamma(x, 1, 2),
  y8 = dgamma(x, 1, 1),
  y9 = dgamma(x, 1, 0.5),
  y10 = dgamma(x, 1, 0.1)
)
labels <- c(
  "scale = 0.5, rate = 2",
  "scale = 1, rate = 2",
  "scale = 3, rate = 2",
  "scale = 5, rate = 2",
  "scale = 7, rate = 2"
)

color <- viridis::cividis(length(labels))

data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y1, color = labels[1]), size = 1) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y2, color = labels[2]), size = 1) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y3, color = labels[3]), size = 1) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y4, color = labels[4]), size = 1) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y5, color = labels[5]), size = 1) +
  guides(color = guide_legend(title = "Parameter")) +
  ggtitle(
    "Distribusi Gamma\ndengan beberapa parameter"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() + ylab("f(x)") +ylim(0,2.2)

labels <- c(
  "scale = 1, rate = 3",
  "scale = 1, rate = 2",
  "scale = 1, rate = 1",
  "scale = 1, rate = 0.5",
  "scale = 1, rate = 0.1"
)

color <- viridis::cividis(length(labels))

data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y6, color = labels[1]), size = 1) +

  geom_line(aes(y = y8, color = labels[3]), size = 1) +

Distribusi Geometri

\((1-p)^k p\) dimana \(k \in {0,1,2,3...}\)

x <- seq(0,10)

data <- data.frame(
  x = x,
  y1 = dgeom(x, 0.1),
  y2 = dgeom(x, 0.2),
  y3 = dgeom(x, 0.5),
  y4 = dgeom(x, 0.7),
  y5 = dgeom(x, 0.9)
)

labels <- c('0.1', '0.2', '0.5', '0.7', '0.9')

data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y1, color = labels[1]), size = 1.1, alpha = 0.8) +
  geom_point(aes(y = y1, color = labels[1]), size = 2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y2, color = labels[2]), size = 1.1, alpha = 0.8) +
  geom_point(aes(y = y2, color = labels[2]), size = 2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y3, color = labels[3]), size = 1.1, alpha = 0.8) +
  geom_point(aes(y = y3, color = labels[3]), size = 2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y4, color = labels[4]), size = 1.1, alpha = 0.8) +
  geom_point(aes(y = y4, color = labels[4]), size = 2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y5, color = labels[5]), size = 1.1, alpha = 0.8) +
  geom_point(aes(y = y5, color = labels[5]), size = 2) +
  guides(color = guide_legend(title = "Parameter P")) +
  ggtitle(
    "Distribusi Geometri",
    "Parameter P mengubah titik awal dan skewness dari distribusinya"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() + ylab("f(x)")

Distribusi HiperGeometri

Distribusi ini memiliki 3 parameter pada PDF nya

  • N = Jumlah Kejadian
  • n = Banyaknya percobaan
  • k = Jumlah Kejadian sukses
  • dan random variabel x = Kejadian sukses yang diinginkan dari banyaknya percobaan

Contoh, jika kita memiliki 100 bola, dan 10 bola diantaranya cacat, maka berapakah peluang pengambilan 30 bola, 5 diantaranya cacat?

  • N = 100
  • k = 10
  • n = 30
  • x = 5

\(f(x; N, k, n) = \displaystyle \frac{\binom{k}{x}\binom{N-k}{n-x}}{\binom{N}{n}}\)

N <- 500
k <- c(50, 100, 200, 400)
n <- 200

x <- seq(0,n)

data <- data.frame(
  y1 = dhyper(x, m = k[1], n = N-k[1], k = n),
  y2 = dhyper(x, m = k[2], n = N-k[2], k = n),
  y3 = dhyper(x, m = k[3], n = N-k[3], k = n),
  y4 = dhyper(x, m = k[4], n = N-k[4], k = n)
)

data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y1)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y2)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y3))

Distribusi Normal

x <- seq(-20,20,0.01)

data <- data.frame(
  x  = x,
  y1 = dnorm(x, -10, 1),
  y2 = dnorm(x, 10, 1),
  y3 = dnorm(x, 0, 0.5),
  y4 = dnorm(x, 0, 2),
  y5 = dnorm(x, 0, 4)
)
labels <- c(
  'mean = -10, sd = 1  ',
  'mean =  10, sd = 1  ',
  'mean =   0, sd = 0.5',
  'mean =   0, sd = 2  ',
  'mean =   0, sd = 4  '
)


data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x)) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y1, color = labels[1]), size = 1.5) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y2, color = labels[2]), size = 1.5) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y3, color = labels[3]), size = 1.5) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y4, color = labels[4]), size = 1.5) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y5, color = labels[5]), size = 1.5) +
  guides(color = guide_legend(title = "Parameter")) +
  theme_minimal() + ylab("f(x)") + ggtitle(
    'Distribusi Normal',
    'Mean mengubah lokasi distribusinya, dan sd mengubah scale distribusinya'
  )

Distribusi uniform

data <- data.frame(
  x1 = pracma::linspace(-3,2,100),
  y1 = dunif(pracma::linspace(-3,2,100), -3, 2),
  x2 = pracma::linspace(4,5,100),
  y2 = dunif(pracma::linspace(4,5,100), 4, 5)
)

data %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_col(aes(x1, y1, fill = "a = -3, b = 2"), width = 0.1) +
  geom_col(aes(x2, y2, fill = "a = 4, b = 5")) +
  guides(fill = guide_legend(title = "Parameter")) +
  ylab("f(x)") + theme_minimal() + ggtitle(
    'Distribusi Uniform'
  )

Distribusi Poisson

x <- seq(0,20)

data <- data.frame(
  x = x,
  y1 = dpois(x, 1),
  y2 = dpois(x, 4),
  y3 = dpois(x, 9)
)

data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = x)) + 
  geom_line(aes(y = y1, color = "1"), size = 1.1) +
  geom_point(aes(y = y1, color = "1"), shape = 0, size = 2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y2, color = "4"), size = 1.1) +
  geom_point(aes(y = y2, color = "4"), shape = 0, size = 2) +
  geom_line(aes(y = y3, color = "9"), size = 1.1) +
  geom_point(aes(y = y3, color = "9"), shape = 0, size = 2) +
  theme_minimal() + ylab("f(x)") + ggtitle(
    "Distribusi Poisson",
    "Lambda memngaruhi kemencengan dan scale dari distribusinya"
  ) + guides(color = guide_legend(
    title = "Lambda"
  ))
